<p>GDP growth: 2.7% GDP: $43bn (PPP: $63bn) Inflation: 2.8% Population: 3.2m GDP per head: $13,500 (PPP: $19,800)</p>

<p>The centre-right Homeland Union-Lithuanian Christian Democrats dominate policymaking in the minority coalition government, but divisions within both the party and the coalition mean the odds are slim of its surviving until the October elections. Its successor will be no more stable. Austerity is in order as the economy climbs back from its 2009 tumble, but the protests this government has faced will recur. Economic growth will be modest, though impressive next to the 14.9% contraction of 2009.</p>

